## 🔍 **Comprehensive Accessibility Test Results for Emoji Picker Category Icons**

### **Test: Keyboard Accessibility of Category Icons (Tab Navigation)**

**URL tested**: `http://localhost:6006/iframe.html?id=picker--default&viewMode=story`

---

### **1. Element Structure (HTML)**

The emoji picker category icons are implemented as:
```html
<div class="emoji-mart-bar">           ← NO role="navigation", NO aria-label
  <div class="emoji-mart-anchors">     ← NO role, NO aria-label  
    <span title="Frequently Used" 
          data-index="1"
          class="emoji-mart-anchor emoji-mart-anchor-selected"
          style="color: rgb(174, 181, 197);">    ← NO tabindex, NO role="button"
      <div class="emoji-mart-anchor-icon">
        <svg>...</svg>                 ← NO aria-label, NO aria-hidden
      </div>
      <span class="emoji-mart-anchor-bar">...</span>
    </span>
    <span title="Smileys & People" ...>...</span>
    <span title="Animals & Nature" ...>...</span>
    ... etc.
  </div>
</div>
```

---

### **2. Tab Navigation Test Results**

| Tab Press | Focus Goes To | Notes |
|-----------|--------------|-------|
| Tab #1 | **Search input** | Has visible focus cursor indicator ✓ |
| Tab #2 | **Emoji scroll area** | Has visible blue border focus indicator ✓ |
| Tab #3 | **Browser URL bar** | Focus exits the picker entirely |
| **Category icons** | **NEVER FOCUSED** | Completely absent from Tab order ✗ |

---

### **3. Accessibility Issues Found**

| Issue | Severity | Finding |
|-------|----------|---------|
| **Not in tab order** | 🔴 Critical | Category icon `<span>` elements have NO `tabindex` attribute → NOT keyboard focusable |
| **Wrong element type** | 🔴 Critical | Elements are `<span>` with `Role: generic`, NOT `<button>` or `role="button"` |
| **No accessible name** | 🔴 Critical | `Name: ""` (empty) — only has `title` for Description, not Name |
| **No focus indicator** | 🔴 Critical | No CSS `:focus` styles defined for `.emoji-mart-anchor` |
| **No nav role** | 🟡 High | `div.emoji-mart-bar` and `div.emoji-mart-anchors` have NO `role="navigation"` or `<nav>` element |
| **No ARIA attributes** | 🟡 High | No `role`, `aria-label`, `aria-labelledby` on the category icons container |
| **Enter/Space does nothing** | 🔴 Critical | No keyboard event handlers on spans; only `click` handler; pressing Enter/Space can't activate (since elements are not focusable) |

---

### **4. Verification**

- ✓ **Mouse click works**: Clicking category icons successfully switches emoji categories
- ✗ **Tab navigation fails**: Category icons are NOT in the keyboard tab order
- ✗ **Not button elements**: `<span>` with `Role: generic` instead of `<button>` or `role="button"`
- ✗ **No ARIA roles**: No nav landmark, no navigation role, no button role
- ✗ **No visible focus indicator**: No CSS focus styles defined
- ✗ **Enter/Space activation fails**: No keyboard event handlers on category spans

---

Based on this comprehensive testing, the category icons in the emoji picker have **significant keyboard accessibility failures**. They are completely inaccessible via keyboard navigation.

**RESULT: FAIL**

The emoji picker's category icons at the top (Smileys, People, Nature, Foods, Activity, Places, Objects, Symbols, Flags):
1. ❌ **Cannot be reached via Tab key** - not in tab order (no `tabindex`)
2. ❌ **Not implemented as interactive button elements** - `<span>` with `Role: generic`
3. ❌ **No visible focus indicator** - no CSS focus styles
4. ❌ **Enter/Space cannot activate them** - no keyboard event handlers
5. ❌ **No navigation accessibility landmark** - no `<nav>` or `role="navigation"`
